cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a visual tracking algorithm based on a discriminatively trained Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the network iteratively with respect to each domain, which suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves binary classification, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves working with videos, which suggests the involvement of multimedia techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training the network to obtain generic target representations, which suggests the involvement of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category.
